To center a div both horizontally and vertically using CSS Flexbox:

```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
```

For horizontal centering only with margin:
```css
.div {
  margin: 0 auto;
  width: fit-content;
}
```

```python
def is_prime(n):
    if n < 2:
        return False
    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1):
        if n % i == 0:
            return False
    return True
```
This checks divisibility up to √n — more efficient than checking all numbers up to n.

